main event: Two witnesses observed a shiny chrome object moving at a high rate of speed in Falmouth, Mass. on April 1, 1966.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 2 minutes.,The observers utilized an 80 power Gilbert telescope to view the object.,The object was reported to be solitary and shiny chrome in appearance.,Weather balloons were released from Nantucket Island every 6 hours around the time of the sighting.,The witnesses were students at Falmouth High School who reported the object appearing at night.
